---
// AITeamSection.astro
// "The Compound Problem" - why individual AI use doesn't help the team
// POSITION: Between proof strip and three pillars in index.astro
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// EDITORIAL NOTE: Section renamed from "AI Team Problem" to "The Compound Problem"
// to avoid leading with AI as the hero. The insight here is about data + systems
// maturity - AI is the payoff, not the premise.
---

<section class="compound-section section">
  <div class="container">

    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="compound-header fade-up">
      <span class="compound-eyebrow">The Compound Problem</span>
      <h2>
        Your team is already using AI.<br class="headline-break" />
        The problem is they're using it <em>alone</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="compound-intro">
        Disconnected data and no shared workflows mean every operator runs their own isolated experiment. AI amplifies each person's habits - good and bad. The performance gap widens, not narrows.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Before / After Grid -->
    <div class="compound-grid fade-up">

      <!-- WITHOUT foundation -->
      <div class="compound-card compound-card--before">
        <div class="compound-card-header">
          <span class="compound-card-label compound-card-label--problem">Without the foundation</span>
          <h3>AI works for individuals. Not the team.</h3>
        </div>

        <ul class="compound-list">
          <li class="compound-list-item compound-list-item--problem">
            <span class="compound-icon compound-icon--problem">✕</span>
            <p><strong>Dirty data</strong> - AI outputs your operators can't trust. They ignore them.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="compound-list-item compound-list-item--problem">
            <span class="compound-icon compound-icon--problem">✕</span>
            <p><strong>Disconnected systems</strong> - AI sees a fragment of the deal. Context always missing.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="compound-list-item compound-list-item--problem">
            <span class="compound-icon compound-icon--problem">✕</span>
            <p><strong>No shared playbooks</strong> - every operator reinvents the same prompts from scratch, every day.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="compound-list-item compound-list-item--problem">
            <span class="compound-icon compound-icon--problem">✕</span>
            <p><strong>Widening gap</strong> - your best operator gets better. Your weakest operator stays exactly where they are.</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- WITH foundation -->
      <div class="compound-card compound-card--after">
        <div class="compound-card-header">
          <span class="compound-card-label compound-card-label--success">With the foundation in place</span>
          <h3>Every operator performs like your best one.</h3>
        </div>

        <ul class="compound-list">
          <li class="compound-list-item compound-list-item--success">
            <span class="compound-icon compound-icon--success">✓</span>
            <p><strong>Clean, structured data</strong> - outputs the team trusts and acts on, immediately.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="compound-list-item compound-list-item--success">
            <span class="compound-icon compound-icon--success">✓</span>
            <p><strong>Connected systems</strong> - full deal context: contacts, history, and signals together.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="compound-list-item compound-list-item--success">
            <span class="compound-icon compound-icon--success">✓</span>
            <p><strong>Shared workflows</strong> - institutional knowledge codified, not locked in one operator's head.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="compound-list-item compound-list-item--success">
            <span class="compound-icon compound-icon--success">✓</span>
            <p><strong>Top-operator logic, distributed</strong> - every seller operates with your best performer's approach.</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Stat callout - tightened, outcome-first -->
    <div class="compound-callout fade-up">
      <div class="compound-callout-inner">
        <div class="compound-stat-block">
          <p class="compound-stat-number">76%</p>
          <p class="compound-stat-label">of CRM data is inaccurate</p>
          <span class="source-tag">CRM Data Report</span>
        </div>
        <div class="compound-text-block">
          <p>
            You can't run a shared intelligence layer on a data swamp. The foundation - clean data, connected systems, structured workflows - is what we build first.
          </p>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-secondary compound-cta">
            Start with the foundation →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* ─── Section container ──────────────────────────────────── */
  .compound-section {
    background-color: var(--page-bg);
  }

  /* ─── Header ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .compound-header {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .compound-eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--sky-blue);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .compound-header h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--heading-color);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .compound-header h2 em {
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--sky-blue);
  }

  .headline-break {
    display: none;
  }

  @media (min-width: 600px) {
    .headline-break {
      display: block;
    }
  }

  .compound-intro {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--muted-text);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ─── Before/After grid ──────────────────────────────────── */
  .compound-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .compound-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  /* ─── Cards ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .compound-card {
    border-radius: var(--card-radius);
    padding: var(--space-7);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .compound-card--before {
    background-color: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.16);
  }

  .compound-card--after {
    background-color: rgba(200, 240, 74, 0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(200, 240, 74, 0.16);
  }

  /* Card header */
  .compound-card-header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-5);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .compound-card-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }

  .compound-card-label--problem { color: var(--warning-red); }
  .compound-card-label--success { color: var(--emerald); }

  .compound-card-header h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--heading-color);
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* List */
  .compound-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    flex: 1;
  }

  .compound-list-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .compound-icon {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 1px;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .compound-icon--problem {
    background-color: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.12);
    color: var(--warning-red);
  }

  .compound-icon--success {
    background-color: rgba(200, 240, 74, 0.12);
    color: var(--emerald);
  }

  .compound-list-item p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--muted-text);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .compound-list-item strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-color);
  }

  /* ─── Stat callout ───────────────────────────────────────── */
  .compound-callout {
    background-color: var(--navy);
    border-radius: var(--card-radius);
    padding: var(--space-7);
    box-shadow: var(--glow-blue);
  }

  .compound-callout-inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-7);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .compound-callout-inner {
      flex-direction: row;
      align-items: center;
    }
  }

  .compound-stat-block {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    text-align: center;
    min-width: 120px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .compound-stat-block {
      padding-right: var(--space-7);
      border-right: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }
  }

  .compound-stat-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--sky-blue);
    line-height: 1;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
  }

  .compound-stat-label {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
  }

  .compound-text-block {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .compound-text-block p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .compound-cta {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border-color: var(--sky-blue);
    color: var(--sky-blue);
  }

  .compound-cta:hover {
    background-color: var(--sky-blue);
    color: var(--navy);
  }

  /* source-tag inherits from global.css */
</style>
